ðŸ”¥ What WOULD Bring Data to the Driver?
    -> collect() , take() , first()
    -> show()   // partially
    -> count()  // only returns a number
 ** write file after transformation is done by Executor, not bring back to Driver

ðŸš¨ When Driver Crashes
    -> 1ï¸âƒ£ Using collect() -> If dataset is huge -> Entire data is sent to driver -> Driver OOM -> Job Crashes
    -> 3ï¸âƒ£ Large Broadcast Variable -> Driver first collects it, then distribute -> Driver OOM possible

ðŸ”¹ Case 1: Input Data > Executor Memory
    This is common and usually handled gracefully by Spark.
    âœ… What Spark Does
        Spark does not load entire dataset into memory at once. It Splits data into partitions
        Processes one partition at a time per executor
    Uses:
        Memory & Disk spill (if memory is insufficient)

ðŸ”¥ If Memory Is Not Enough
1ï¸âƒ£ Spill to Disk
        For operations like:
    -> Shuffle / Sort / Join / Aggregation
    -> Spark spills intermediate data to disk automatically.

2ï¸âƒ£ OutOfMemoryError (Executor OOM)
    -> A single partition is too large
    -> Data skew
    -> Huge collect inside transformation
    -> Broadcast table too big

ðŸ”¹ Schema Evolution:
    Schema evolution is the ability of a data system to handle changes in the structure (schema)
    of data over time without breaking existing pipelines or queries.
    ðŸ”¹ Types of Schema Changes
        âœ… 1. Add Column (Most Common) :  Add new nullable column.
        âœ… 2. Remove Column :  May hide column (physical deletion depends on format).
        âœ… 3. Rename Column :  Supported in advanced table formats like Delta.
        âœ… 4. Change Data Type :  Limited support (e.g., INT â†’ LONG may work).
    spark.read.option("mergeSchema", "true").parquet("users")
    df.write.format("delta").option("mergeSchema", "true").mode("append").save("users_delta")

ðŸ”¹ Narrow Transformation vs Wide Transformation
    -> map() , filter() , flatMap() , mapPartitions() , union()
    -> groupByKey() , reduceByKey() , distinct() , join() , repartition() , sortByKey()